Constructor & Destructor Documentation

CUInt128::CUInt128 ( const CUInt128 &  value,
uint32_t  numBits 
)

Generates a new number, copying the most significant 'numBits' bits from 'value'.

The remaining bits are randomly generated.

References GetBitNumber(), and SetBitNumber().

void CUInt128::StoreCryptValue ( uint8_t *  buf  )  const

Stores value used by the crypt functions.

Since eMule started to use the value as-is (four little-endian 32-bit integers in big-endian order), we have to reproduce that same representation on every platform.

Parameters:
buf Buffer to hold the value. Must be large enough to hold the data (16 bytes at least), and must not be NULL.
